  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed roof extension, by virtue of its design, bulk and massing would appear as a dominant and discordant form of development that would detract from the character and appearance of the host building, the symmetry of this pair of semi-detached houses and the uniformity of this group of houses No.5-19 (odd) Broomfield Avenue. The proposed development therefore fails to preserve and enhance the character and appearance of the Lakes Estate Conservation Area and the visual amenities of the street scene and the surrounding area. This is contrary to Sections 12 and 16 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policies D3 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CP30 of the Enfield Core Strategy (2010) and Policies DMD8, DMD13, DMD37 and DMD44 of the Enfield Development Management Document (2014)."
  ],
